name: adenosylcobinamide-phosphate synthase
reaction: (1) ATP + adenosylcobyric acid + (R)-1-aminopropan-2-yl phosphate = ADP + phosphate + adenosylcobinamide phosphate [RN:R06529]; (2) ATP + adenosylcobyric acid + (R)-1-aminopropan-2-ol = ADP + phosphate + adenosylcobinamide [RN:R07302]
comment: One of the substrates for this reaction, (R)-1-aminopropan-2-yl phosphate, is produced by CobD (EC 4.1.1.81, threonine-phosphate decarboxylase).

references.title: Three-dimensional structure of the L-threonine-O-3-phosphate decarboxylase (CobD) enzyme from Salmonella enterica.
